Provenance of ported numerical routines in crates/core
=====================================================

This crate uses one audited dependency exception for SHA-256: RustCrypto
`sha2` 0.11.0 with default features disabled. It and its locked normal
transitive closure are sourced from crates.io under MIT OR Apache-2.0:
`sha2` 0.11.0 (RustCrypto/hashes), `digest` 0.11.3 and `crypto-common` 0.2.2
(RustCrypto/traits), `block-buffer` 0.12.1 and `cpufeatures` 0.3.0
(RustCrypto/utils), `hybrid-array` 0.4.13 (RustCrypto/hybrid-array), `typenum`
1.20.1 (paholg/typenum), `cfg-if` 1.0.4 (rust-lang/cfg-if), and target-only
`libc` 0.2.186 (rust-lang/libc). Exact checksums are locked in `Cargo.lock`;
the audit decision and update policy are in `docs/sha2-fingerprint-spike.md`.

